org.team1540.base.power

Class PowerManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Thread
      • org.team1540.base.power.PowerManager
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Sendable, Runnable

    public class PowerManager
extends Thread
implements Sendable
    A class for power managing PowerManageables (both with and without telemetry.) Set a target voltage to stay above, register PowerManageables, and you're good to go!

      • isVoltageDipping

        public boolean isVoltageDipping()
        Determines if the voltage is currently dipping. If power limiting is not engaged, returns RobotController.getBatteryVoltage() < voltageDipLow || RobotController.isBrownedOut(); If power limiting is engaged, returns PowerDistributionPanel.getVoltage() < voltageDipLow + voltageMargin || RobotController.isBrownedOut();
        Returns:
        Boolean representing if the voltage is dipping.
